"```sql\nSELECT Patient.Diagnosis, Laboratory.Date\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Patient.ID = 30609;\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the diagnosis of the patient with ID '30609' from the `Patient` table and lists all the dates of laboratory tests done for this patient from the `Laboratory` table. The query uses a JOIN operation to connect the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables based on the foreign key relationship."